    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\nc_T\n=\n\\left[\n\\frac{1}{2\\pi}F\n\\right]\n\\in\nH^2(M\\setminus\\{p\\},\\mathbb{Z}) .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $F$ be the curvature two-form of a principal $U(1)$ bundle over the punctured manifold $M\\setminus\\{p\\}$.\n\nFor a $U(1)$ bundle, the first characteristic class is obtained by normalizing curvature by $2\\pi$:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\frac{1}{2\\pi}F .\n\\end{equation}\n\nTaking the cohomology class gives:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nc_T\n=\n\\left[\n\\frac{1}{2\\pi}F\n\\right].\n\\end{equation}\n\nSince the TZP is removed from the base space, the class naturally lives in:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nH^2(M\\setminus\\{p\\},\\mathbb{Z}) .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThus,\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\nc_T\n=\n\\left[\n\\frac{1}{2\\pi}F\n\\right]\n\\in\nH^2(M\\setminus\\{p\\},\\mathbb{Z}) .\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThe Trawin characteristic class records the topological charge generated by removing the TZP from the manifold.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
